<concept id="concept_1BCF5C425D7D4627AB1C66A085CF6E11"
                xml:lang="en-us">
        <title>Installing the <ph audience="ror">ROR</ph><ph audience="aws">AWS</ph><ph audience="os">OpenStack</ph><ph
                        audience="tps5">TPS5</ph><ph audience="vmware">vSphere</ph> Integration Software</title>
        <conbody>
                <p>The following sections describe how to install and configure the <ph audience="ror">ROR</ph><ph
                                audience="aws">AWS</ph><ph audience="os">OpenStack</ph><ph audience="tps5">TPS5</ph><ph
                                audience="vmware"
                        >vSphere</ph> integration software as well as the preparations you need to take beforehand.</p>
                <p>Installing the <ph audience="ror">ROR</ph><ph audience="aws">AWS</ph><ph audience="os"
                                >OpenStack</ph><ph audience="tps5">TPS5</ph><ph audience="vmware"
                                >vSphere</ph> integration software consists of installing APP<ph audience="ror"
                                > and registering the ROR</ph><ph audience="aws"> and registering the AWS</ph><ph
                                audience="os"> and registering the OpenStack</ph><ph audience="tps5"
                                > and registering the TPS5</ph><ph audience="vmware"
                                >, registering the VMware</ph> service controller<ph audience="vmware"
                                > and setting up a database for the controller</ph>. </p>
                <p audience="doc">If you already have a working APP installation in your environment, proceed as described in <xref
                                href="c_InstControllerInExistingAPP.xml"/>.</p>

        </conbody>
</concept>
